This paper deals with wireless networks and their performance in terms of reliability, latency, and throughput. The main focus is on grant-free access, which is a technique used to reduce latency in cellular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY) as it deals with optimizing the performance of wireless networks. Additionally, it discusses security issues (cs.CR) related to grant-free access. Finally, the paper mentions industrial automation (cs.MM) as one of the applications of wireless networks.
